		{
			"id": 1,
			"parent": 0,
			"text": "This study concerns 9 iv drug abusers with acquired immunodeficiency syndrome ( AIDS ) who developed hypercortisolism without the clinical signs or metabolic consequences of hypercortisolism . <S>",
			"relation": "ROOT",
			"tag": "Hypothesis-Objective"
		},
		{
			"id": 2,
			"parent": 1,
			"text": "All patients were characterized by an Addisonian picture ( weakness , weight loss , hypotension , hyponatremia , and intense mucocutaneous melanosis ) . <S>",
			"relation": "ELABORATION",
			"tag": "Background"
		},
		{
			"id": 3,
			"parent": 1,
			"text": "An acquired form of peripheral resistance to glucocorticoids was suspected . <S>",
			"relation": "ELABORATION",
			"tag": "Background"
		},
		{
			"id": 4,
			"parent": 1,
			"text": "We , therefore , examined glucocorticoid receptor characteristics on mononuclear leukocytes",
			"relation": "VERIFICATION",
			"tag": "Hypothesis-Objective"
		},
		{
			"id": 5,
			"parent": 4,
			"text": "by measuring [3H]dexamethasone binding and the effect of dexamethasone on [3H]thymidine incorporation , which is one of the effects of glucocorticoid receptor activation . <S>",
			"relation": "MANNER-MEANS",
			"tag": "Verification-Method"
		},
		{
			"id": 6,
			"parent": 4,
			"text": "Glucocorticoid receptor density was increased in AIDS patients with an Addisonian picture ( group 1 ; 16.2 +/- 9.4 fmol/million cells )",
			"relation": "CAUSE-RESULT",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 7,
			"parent": 6,
			"text": "compared to values in 12 AIDS patients without an Addisonian picture ( group 2 ; 6.05 +/- 2.6 fmol/million cells ; P less than 0.01 ) and sex- and age-matched controls ( 3.15 +/- 2.3 fmol/million cells ; P less than 0.01 ) . <S>",
			"relation": "COMPARISON",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 8,
			"parent": 6,
			"text": "The affinity of glucocorticoid receptors ( Kd ) was strikingly decreased ( 9.36 +/- 3.44 nM in group 1 ; 3.2 +/- 1.5 nM in group 2 ; 2.0 +/- 0.8 nM in controls ; P less than 0.01 ) . <S>",
			"relation": "ADDITION",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 9,
			"parent": 6,
			"text": "[3H]Thymidine incorporation was decreased dose-dependently by dexamethasone in controls and patients ;",
			"relation": "ADDITION",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 10,
			"parent": 9,
			"text": "the effect was significantly blunted ( P less than 0.05 ) in group 1 patients ,",
			"relation": "COMPARISON",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 11,
			"parent": 9,
			"text": "which suggests",
			"relation": "CAUSE-RESULT",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 12,
			"parent": 11,
			"text": "that activation of glucocorticoid receptor is impaired",
			"relation": "ATTRIBUTION",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 13,
			"parent": 12,
			"text": "as a result of the glucocorticoid receptor abnormality . <S>",
			"relation": "CAUSE-RESULT",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 14,
			"parent": 1,
			"text": "In conclusion , AIDS patients with hypercortisolism and clinical features of peripheral resistance to glucocorticoids are characterized by abnormal glucocorticoid receptors on lymphocytes . <S>",
			"relation": "CONCLUSION",
			"tag": "Conclusion"
		},
		{
			"id": 15,
			"parent": 14,
			"text": "Resistance to glucocorticoids implies a complex change in immune-endocrine function , which may be important in the course of immunodeficiency syndrome . <S>",
			"relation": "ADDITION",
			"tag": "Conclusion"
		}
	]
}